<dl id="n36212d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36212d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36212d"> 212(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sashed to chin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I swear to thee, worthy reader, if history and tradition belie not this warrior <font color="green">[General Van Poffenburgh]</font>, I would give all the money in my pocket to have seen him accoutred <i>cap-&agrave;-pie</i>,&mdash;booted to the middle, <mark>sashed to the chin</mark>, crowned with an overshadowing cocked hat, and girded with a leathern belt ten inches broad, from which trailed a falchion, of a length I dare not mention. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 254</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: pencil mark through &lsquo;clean&rsquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
